  "assistantText": "Perfect! ✅ **Counter with 7-segment display built successfully.**\n\n## Wiring Table\n\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Purpose |\n|-------------|-----------|---------|\n| D2 | 7-Segment | Segment A |\n| D3 | 7-Segment | Segment B |\n| D4 | 7-Segment | Segment C |\n| D5 | 7-Segment | Segment D |\n| D6 | 7-Segment | Segment E |\n| D7 | 7-Segment | Segment F |\n| D8 | 7-Segment | Segment G |\n| D9 | Button | Add (increment) |\n| GND | 7-Segment | Common cathode |\n| GND | Button | Ground return |\n\n## How It Works\n\nThe sketch counts from 0–9 on the 7-segment display. Press the button to increment the counter; it wraps back to 0 after 9. Each segment is directly driven from an Arduino pin with internal control—no series resistors needed in this simplified display. Button uses `INPUT_PULLUP` and detects a LOW press state with debounce.",
